Aviva Approached Eric Daniels on Chairman’s Role, Sky Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-17T21:42:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/aviva-approached-eric-daniels-on-chairman-s-role-sky-reports.html
  Aviva Plc (AV/)  has approached  Eric Daniels , former  Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  Chief Executive
Officer, about becoming its chairman, Sky News City Editor Mark
Kleinman  reported  in his blog on the website, without
attribution. Daniels is one of five people on a shortlist being
considered by Aviva directors, Kleinman said, without saying
where he got the information.  Lloyds Banking Group spokeswoman Sarah Swailes declined to
comment when contacted by telephone, and a call to Aviva Plc
Group Communications Director Nigel Prideaux out of office hours
wasn’t immediately returned.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 